{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/logistic-regression-for-classification-task-f143a5a67785", "time": 1683010800.104054, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/logistic-regression-for-classification-task-f143a5a67785/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Logistic Regression for Classification Task | by Mengsay Loem | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Logistic Regression for Classification Task", "description": "With pattern recognition approach, there are many methods to implement a handwriting digits recognition task. In my previous stories, I have introduced the Linear Discriminant Analysis base on the\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/handwritten-khmer-digit-recognition-860edf06cd57", "anchor_text": "previous stories", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/handwritten-khmer-digit-recognition-860edf06cd57", "anchor_text": "Fisher\u2019s linear discriminant analysis", "paragraph_index": 11}], "all_paragraphs": ["With pattern recognition approach, there are many methods to implement a handwriting digits recognition task. In my previous stories, I have introduced the Linear Discriminant Analysis base on the Gaussian model maximum likelihood estimation. In this post, I apply the Logistic Regression model on the English numeral handwriting digits recognition task.", "In the logistic regression model, an occurrence probability of an event is represented by a logistic function. For example, in a two-class problem, the logistic sigmoid function is commonly used. In a multi-class problem, softmax function is known to offer good performance.", "In this text, we introduce how a posteriori probability can be represented in logistic function. Next, we imply a linear transformation of each category to input patterns and estimate their posteriori probabilities.", "Consider a classification task with the number of classes C. Using maximum a posteriori probability rule, the output category of an input pattern x is the category y where p(y|x) is maximum. A posteriori probability p(y=i|x) is", "softmax(\u30fb) is called a softmax function. When, C=2, it is known as a logistic sigmoid function. From (3), we can confirm that a posteriori probability can be represented by a logistic function.", "In a multi-class task, we use a softmax function, p(y=i|x)=softmax(a_i). To estimate this probability, we estimate a_i by a linear transformation of the input pattern into i-th category. This means,", "where parameter w_i is estimated by the maximum likelihood method.", "Now, the posteriori probability p(y=i|x) is", "Let C be the number of categories, {(x_i,y_i)} (i=1,\u2026,N) be sample data set. Likelihood function is", "To define the optimal parameter w_j we calculate the gradient of the log-likelihood function.", "However, it is impossible to analytically solve this equation. As a solution, we apply the Gradient Ascent learning algorithm to maximize the log-likelihood function. The learning algorithm is", "Now let\u2019s see how recognition accuracy improved compared to Fisher\u2019s linear discriminant analysis.", "From the experiment results, the accuracy of recognition is improved with the logistic regression model.", "In Fisher\u2019s LDA, the variance-covariance of all category is assumed to be equal. As a result, there is a lack of information from each category features. However, Fisher\u2019s LDA is an extremely simple model that consumes less computation time.", "In the Logistic Regression model, the concept of a linear transformation of input into each category is a form of linear discriminatory rule which also found in the linear is similar to Fisher\u2019s LDA. The feature of the Logistic Regression model is applying a logistic function to estimate a posteriori probability. This benefits in increasing the degree of freedom in data feature representation. However, since we cannot directly obtain the optimal parameter of the linear transformation of Logistic Regression with analytical calculation, the time computation in Gradient Ascent learning is a demerit. Also, this learning rule is a numerical calculation where only approximate parameters are obtained, the result tends to change depending on the initialization.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Master's Student @ Tokyo Tech | Dept. of Computer Science"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Ff143a5a67785&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Flogistic-regression-for-classification-task-f143a5a67785&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Flogistic-regression-for-classification-task-f143a5a67785&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Flogistic-regression-for-classification-task-f143a5a67785&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redi